          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1641911086116-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and 175ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice and meat is cooked (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more water if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1641911094867-x200.jpg",
